../openclaw_state_fb3451db-7b3e-469a-be08-96011860805a/agents/metaclaw_agent/sessions/day15_d17f0df1-a277-48b5-949e-552409453dde.jsonl:24:{"type":"message","id":"c00b572b","parentId":"e5f3264e","timestamp":"2026-03-17T05:10:02.569Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_stlGwFfLtoaLvIX5ERzTpZMe","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"day15/20260403_q2_kickoff_plan.md","content":"---\ntitle: \"Q2 2026 Kickoff Plan (Apr–Jun)\"\nsprint: \"Sprint 8 Week 2 Wrap-up / Q2 Kickoff\"\nowner: \"Backend Engineering (Alex Zhang)\"\ndate: \"2026-04-03\"\n---\n\n# Q2 (April–June) Kickoff Plan\n\n## 1) Q2 Goals\n\n### Product & Delivery\n- **Ship high-impact collaboration improvements** with predictable weekly releases.\n- **Reduce cycle time** from spec → release by tightening handoffs (PM ↔ Eng ↔ QA).\n- **Improve platform reliability** by addressing top recurring incidents and performance bottlenecks.\n\n### Engineering Excellence\n- **Strengthen API governance** (versioning, deprecation policy, changelog discipline).\n- **Improve data quality & observability** for core usage metrics and operational dashboards.\n- **Reduce tech debt in configuration and reporting pipelines** to enable faster iteration.\n\n### Customer Outcomes\n- **Increase adoption of key workflows** (project templates, activity tracking, reporting).\n- **Improve enterprise readiness** (auditability, role/permission clarity, operational reporting).\n\n## 2) Key Projects (Q2)\n\n### A. API Governance & Compatibility\n**Objective:** Make API evolution safe and predictable.\n- Deliverables\n  - API versioning guidelines + ADR alignment\n  - Deprecation & changelog process\n  - Backward-compatible changes checklist for reviews\n- Success metrics\n  - Zero breaking changes in minor releases\n  - ≥90% endpoints documented with versioning notes\n\n### B. Usage Analytics + Operational Reporting\n**Objective:** Provide trustworthy metrics for product decisions and stakeholder reporting.\n- Deliverables\n  - Standardized weekly/monthly reporting JSON outputs\n  - Data validation checks for event ingestion and aggregation\n  - Dashboard-ready data extracts (usage, activity, error stats)\n- Success metrics\n  - Data completeness ≥99% for core events\n  - Automated validation gates for reporting artifacts\n\n### C. Reliability & Performance Improvements\n**Objective:** Reduce incident volume and improve response time.\n- Deliverables\n  - Top-5 error class remediation plan (root causes + fixes)\n  - Latency audit for critical endpoints\n  - Logging improvements + actionable alerts\n- Success metrics\n  - ≥30% reduction in recurring errors vs Q1 baseline\n  - P95 latency improvements on top endpoints (target to be set after audit)\n\n### D. Developer Productivity & Configuration Refactor\n**Objective:** Reduce friction in config changes and reporting workflows.\n- Deliverables\n  - Config loader consolidation / refactor (with tests)\n  - Build a reusable report generation pipeline\n  - Documentation updates (onboarding, runbooks)\n- Success metrics\n  - Faster environment setup time (target: <30 minutes end-to-end)\n  - Reduced config-related regressions\n\n## 3) Milestone Schedule (April–June)\n\n> Dates are planned checkpoints; final sequencing should be confirmed during Q2 kickoff grooming.\n\n### April (Stabilize + Foundation)\n- **Week 1 (Apr 6–10): Kickoff + planning**\n  - Confirm Q2 scope, owners, and success metrics\n  - Lock reporting artifact standards (naming + meta + timestamps)\n- **Week 2–3 (Apr 13–24): API governance**\n  - Finalize versioning & deprecation process\n  - Add review checklist to PR template\n- **Week 4 (Apr 27–30): Reliability baseline**\n  - Identify top recurring error classes\n  - Define performance test plan for critical endpoints\n\n### May (Execution + Incremental Releases)\n- **Week 1–2 (May 4–15): Analytics + validation**\n  - Implement validator gates for reporting outputs\n  - Improve data quality checks and error tracking\n- **Week 3 (May 18–22): Performance improvements**\n  - Optimize highest-traffic endpoints\n  - Logging and alert tuning\n- **Week 4 (May 25–29): Mid-quarter review**\n  - Reassess scope, adjust milestones, report to PM\n\n### June (Hardening + Q2 Closeout)\n- **Week 1–2 (Jun 1–12): Reliability hardening**\n  - Close remaining top error classes\n  - Ensure monitoring and runbooks are in place\n- **Week 3 (Jun 15–19): Final feature push**\n  - Complete remaining Q2 commitments\n  - Documentation polish and onboarding updates\n- **Week 4 (Jun 22–30): Q2 wrap-up**\n  - Final metrics report, retrospectives, Q3 seeds\n\n## 4) Roles & Ownership (Initial)\n\n- **Backend (Owner: Alex)**\n  - API governance, reporting pipeline, reliability remediation\n- **Frontend (Owner: Chen)**\n  - UI workflow improvements aligned to key projects\n- **QA (Owner: Dana)**\n  - Release validation, regression suite updates, validation gates\n- **Backend Engineer (Bai)**\n  - Analytics pipeline implementation + data validation tooling\n\n## 5) Risks & Mitigations\n\n- **Risk:** Scope creep from ad-hoc stakeholder requests\n  - *Mitigation:* Weekly scope review; require written acceptance criteria before starting new work\n- **Risk:** Data quality issues undermine reporting trust\n  - *Mitigation:* Validation gates + clear ownership for data sources\n- **Risk:** Reliability work deprioritized by feature demand\n  - *Mitigation:* Reserve capacity each sprint for error-class remediation\n\n## 6) Next Actions (for Kickoff Meeting)\n\n1. Confirm Q2 goals and success metrics with PM.\n2. Finalize project owners and milestones per sprint.\n3. Agree on reporting standards (file naming, meta object, timestamp formats).\n4. Create Sprint 9 backlog: top items for April Week 1–2.\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"metaclaw","model":"gpt-5.2","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"