../openclaw_state_74b13016-5b12-405a-8784-ba8654042ac6/agents/metaclaw_agent/sessions/day20_4a0ece6a-e1a5-4d84-99ba-46b47ac8d581.jsonl:74:{"type":"message","id":"2c8eae99","parentId":"2a308967","timestamp":"2026-03-17T05:26:33.015Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_DRF5T3kKvMH6EGWo4Rk64KUa","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"day20/20260410_sprint9_week1_review_presentation.md","content":"# Sprint 9 — Week 1 Sprint Review (Apr 10, 2026)\n\n## Agenda\n\n1. Sprint goal & outcomes\n2. Achievements (what shipped)\n3. Demo highlights\n4. Metrics / performance\n5. Risks & follow-ups\n6. Q&A\n\n---\n\n## Sprint Goal & Outcome\n\n- **Sprint**: Sprint 9, Week 1\n- **Goal**: Stabilize core platform improvements and prepare for Sprint Review\n- **Outcome**: **Goal achieved** — major planned deliverables completed; ready for review and Week 2 planning.\n\n---\n\n## This Week’s Achievements\n\n- Deployed **refactored authentication module**\n- Completed **migration of legacy database tables**\n- Fixed a **critical performance bottleneck in the API layer**\n\nAdditional execution notes:\n- CI build timeout updated to reduce false failures on slower runners\n- New dashboard feature flag enabled for rollout readiness\n\n---\n\n## Demo Highlights\n\n### 1) Authentication Module (Refactor)\n\n**What to show**\n- Login / token refresh flow\n- Permissions/role checks on a protected endpoint\n\n**What to say**\n- Refactor improves maintainability and reduces duplicated auth logic\n- Clearer separation between authentication and authorization\n\n### 2) Legacy DB Table Migration\n\n**What to show**\n- Before/after schema or migration status output\n- A representative query path confirming reads/writes work as expected\n\n**What to say**\n- Migration reduces operational overhead and unblocks future schema evolution\n- Rollback strategy confirmed and documented\n\n### 3) API Performance Improvement\n\n**What to show**\n- Endpoint latency comparison (before vs after)\n- p99 tracking and how we monitor regressions\n\n**What to say**\n- Bottleneck fix improves tail latency and reliability under load\n- Next step: iterate toward p99 target\n\n---\n\n## Metrics / Performance\n\n- **Primary metric**: API p99 response time (ms)\n- **Target**: p99 ≤ 200 ms\n- **Status**: trending down, but still above target — continue optimization in Week 2\n\n---\n\n## Risks & Follow-ups\n\n- Performance remains above target p99; ensure continued profiling and regression tests\n- Confirm integration tests + security scan completion before next production push\n\n---\n\n## Q&A Preparation\n\n### Likely Questions & Suggested Answers\n\n1. **“Is the auth refactor fully backward-compatible?”**\n   - Yes for current clients; we maintained existing contracts and added regression coverage where applicable.\n\n2. **“What’s the rollback plan for the DB migration?”**\n   - Backups + reversible migrations where possible; rollout staged to reduce blast radius.\n\n3. **“Are we meeting SLA targets?”**\n   - We improved tail latency; still working toward p99 ≤ 200 ms. We’ll share updated p99 tracking next week.\n\n4. **“What’s the rollout plan for the new dashboard?”**\n   - Feature-flagged rollout: enable internally first, then staged exposure based on stability metrics.\n\n### Data to Have Ready (If Asked)\n\n- Current p99 measurements and comparison to prior weeks\n- Integration test status + security scan status\n- Migration checklist / verification notes\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"metaclaw","model":"gpt-5.2","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773725180290}}
